div.div: Proposals can form chains and need to fulfill the following restrictions:

- A proposal waits for x block heights before it can be converted by the creator to pass status, i.e., an AccountCell is created; x is the height of the block into which the proposal transaction is packed;
- Proposal n + 1 can be created immediately if it affects 50 AccountCells or contains more than 100 PreAccountCells; -> avoiding a single proposal being too large
- proposal n + 1 must wait x/2 block heights after proposal n to be created if it does not fulfill the previous condition; -> avoid long proposal chains
- Any proposal can be passed by any Keeper;
